00:51:25.719 --> 00:51:29.563
So when the bank gives you a
mortgage it says--so how did

00:51:29.563 --> 00:51:30.730
mortgages work?
 

00:51:30.730 --> 00:51:34.331
It used to be in the old days
that the mortgages were coupon

00:51:34.331 --> 00:51:34.820
bonds.
 

00:51:34.820 --> 00:51:38.469
They'd pay 8,8,
8,8, 8,108, and then what would

00:51:38.469 --> 00:51:43.469
happen is just before the 108
payment everyone would default.

00:51:43.469 --> 00:51:45.822
So in the Depression the people
who defaulted were people who

00:51:45.822 --> 00:51:47.900
defaulted just before their big
principal payment,

00:51:47.900 --> 00:51:50.360
so bankers got wise after the
Depression.

00:51:50.360 --> 00:51:52.289
They said, "Well,
that's a terrible thing to do.

00:51:52.289 --> 00:51:55.400
We should make the payment be
constant and that way there's no

00:51:55.400 --> 00:51:58.407
reason for the guy to default
right at the end and we're not

00:51:58.407 --> 00:52:01.570
going to get stuck with 100
dollars that's not paid."

00:52:01.570 --> 00:52:02.909
So it's constant.
 

00:52:02.909 --> 00:52:05.733
But of course if it's constant
that means the present value of

00:52:05.733 --> 00:52:07.679
what's left is going down all
the time,

00:52:07.679 --> 00:52:10.900
so that's why this number is
going down all the time.

00:52:10.900 --> 00:52:13.141
If it's 108 at the end,
that's why the present value

00:52:13.141 --> 00:52:14.110
would stay the same.
 

00:52:14.110 --> 00:52:18.682
So it's going down all the
time, so that's why it's called

00:52:18.682 --> 00:52:20.690
an amortizing mortgage.
 

00:52:20.690 --> 00:52:23.822
It's because what's left in the
mortgage is getting smaller all

00:52:23.822 --> 00:52:24.380
the time.
 

00:52:24.380 --> 00:52:30.050
So a fixed rate mortgage pays
the same coupon every year.

00:52:30.050 --> 00:52:32.036
The present value of what's
left, therefore,

00:52:32.036 --> 00:52:34.577
must be going down every year
and that's why it's called

00:52:34.577 --> 00:52:35.268
amortizing.
 

00:52:35.268 --> 00:52:38.594
And bankers wanted that to
happen because that way their

00:52:38.594 --> 00:52:40.530
risk is going down every year.
 

00:52:40.530 --> 00:52:43.556
Every year the house is
presumably still worth 120 or

00:52:43.556 --> 00:52:47.164
whatever it was at the beginning
and the amount owed is getting

00:52:47.164 --> 00:52:48.329
lower and lower.
 

00:52:48.329 --> 00:52:51.434
So the bankers are feeling more
and more secure every year

00:52:51.434 --> 00:52:54.650
because the house is backing a
smaller and smaller loan,

00:52:54.650 --> 00:52:56.934
or to put it another way,
if you're uncertain about what

00:52:56.934 --> 00:52:58.929
the price of the house will be
in the future,

00:52:58.929 --> 00:53:01.974
you want to make sure that what
is owed is going down in the

00:53:01.974 --> 00:53:02.440
future.
 

00:53:02.440 --> 00:53:05.643
If the price gradually goes
down of the house what's owed is

00:53:05.643 --> 00:53:07.219
gradually going to go down.
 

00:53:07.219 --> 00:53:10.327
But the main reason why the
number is so important is you

00:53:10.327 --> 00:53:13.822
have to realize the purpose of a
mortgage is you take out a loan

00:53:13.822 --> 00:53:15.710
using the house as collateral.
 

00:53:15.710 --> 00:53:17.349
If you don't make your payment
