00:54:33.268 --> 00:54:35.960
So every year you're paying
part of your principal down.

00:54:35.960 --> 00:54:38.396
That means it's amortizing,
and that means if you want to

00:54:38.396 --> 00:54:41.137
get out of the mortgage you can
get out of it by paying less and

00:54:41.137 --> 00:54:41.530
less.
 

00:54:41.530 --> 00:54:43.438
It means the lender,
the mortgage lender,

00:54:43.438 --> 00:54:46.157
is more and more protected by
the house every year because

00:54:46.157 --> 00:54:47.780
what you owe is less and less.
 

00:54:47.780 --> 00:54:49.610
So that's how a mortgage works.
 

